[143.357393, "o", "    REJECTED: ['The narrative claims Administrator (SID -500) is a human user profile but no citation is provided to support this claim', 'The narrative claims the system is running Windows XP but no citation (e.g., registry key SOFTWARE\\\\Microsoft\\\\Windows NT\\\\CurrentVersion referencing ProductName) is provided to support the OS version', 'The timeline entry for 2008-07-21 01:31:06+00:00 lacks a numbered citation linking it to specific evidence', \"The claim that Administrator is a 'human user profile' is an inference not confirmed by any citation\"]\r\n    Analyst revising...\r\n"]
[162.660119, "o", "    Iteration 1: Skeptic reviewing...\r\n"]
[176.528265, "o", "    REJECTED: ['Timeline entry 1 (2008-07-21 01:30:43 HELPER.EXE) has no corresponding citation in the Evidence section — it references MFT entry 17448-128-4 and prefetch file HELPER.EXE-1D5E6592.pf but no citation number is provided or verified for this claim', 'Timeline entry 2 (2008-07-21 01:31:06 WUAUCLT.EXE) has no corresponding citation in the Evidence section — it references MFT entry 11828-128-4 and WUAUCLT.EXE-399A8E72.pf but no citation number is provided or verified for this claim', \"The timeline entries describe specific forensic artifacts (prefetch files, run counts, MFT entry numbers, last run times) that are presented as confirmed facts but belong in a finding with claim_type 'confirmed' or must be explicitly labeled as inferred; they are not supported by any numbered citation in the Evidence block\", \"The narrative states 'OS version (Windows XP) is inferred from the profile path format' and explicitly acknowledges 'no direct registry citation for ProductName was retrieved' — this admission of an unsupported inference without a citation violates evidence standards for even an informational finding\", \"The finding conflates CONFIRMED artifact data (specific MFT entry numbers, run counts, precise timestamps in the timeline) with the stated claim_type of 'inferred' without clear justification for why high-specificity forensic data appears in the timeline without citations\"]\r\n    FINAL: rejected after 2 iterations\r\n"]
[176.528319, "o", "\r\n  [high] Suspicious Executable HELPER.EXE Executed Multiple Times\r\n"]
[176.529071, "o", "    Iteration 0: Skeptic reviewing...\r\n"]
[190.651366, "o", "    REJECTED: ['Timeline entries for AIM6.EXE (01:30:35, run count 7), AOLSOFTWARE.EXE (01:30:37, run count 10), and FIREFOX.EXE (01:30:38, run count 27) have no supporting citations — only Citation [1] covers HELPER.EXE', \"The narrative claim that HELPER.EXE 'executed within seconds of Firefox, AIM6, and AOLSoftware also being launched' is unsupported because the corroborating timeline entries lack citations\", 'Run counts and execution timestamps for AIM6.EXE, AOLSOFTWARE.EXE, and FIREFOX.EXE are asserted without any cited evidence, violating the requirement that all claims be backed by citations']\r\n    Analyst revising...\r\n"]
[210.791793, "o", "    Iteration 1: Skeptic reviewing...\r\n"]
[232.955919, "o", "    REJECTED: ['MITRE ATT&CK mapping T1567 (Exfiltration Over Web Service) is unsupported by any citation — no evidence of actual data exfiltration is cited, only co-occurrence of application launches', \"The finding is marked 'confirmed' claim type but the central suspicious narrative (exfiltration preparation) is explicitly INFERRED with no supporting citation for data movement or network activity\", 'T1567 rationale conflates application launch timing with exfiltration behavior without citation to network logs, file access records, or other corroborating evidence — this is an unsupported logical leap presented alongside confirmed claims']\r\n    FINAL: rejected after 2 iterations\r\n"]
