[251.005817, "o", "    REJECTED: [\"Narrative claims 'execution of Firefox, AIM, and HELPER.EXE by approximately 46 minutes' after Outlook but no citations are provided for Firefox, AIM, or HELPER.EXE execution times or timestamps\", 'Narrative explicitly names MSOUTL9.OLB and CLIPPIT.ACS as accessed DLLs but no citations are provided to support these two artifacts', \"Claim type is 'confirmed' but MITRE ATT&CK rationale uses speculative language ('may indicate email review or exfiltration'), which is inferential not confirmed — the finding conflates CONFIRMED with INFERRED without justification\", 'Only 2 of the 4 named DLL files (OUTLWVW.DLL, OUTLCTL.DLL) have supporting citations; the other two (MSOUTL9.OLB, CLIPPIT.ACS) are asserted without evidence']\r\n    Analyst revising...\r\n"]
